{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_29","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `fails-javac-compile` job failed, but the evidence suggests the failure happened after a passing candidate was produced. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5933-fails-javac-compile-com.android.tools.build-builder-model-2.2.0-c722ab7b\n\nMost likely failing stage: post-fix job orchestration/finalization, not `javac` anymore. The initial failure was real: `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-20-48-280754Z.log` shows `:compileTestJava` failing with 12 API mismatch errors in `Builder_modelTest.java`, including missing `InstantRun.getIncrementalAssembleTaskName()` and newly required methods such as `Library.isSkipped()`, `BaseConfig.getVersionNameSuffix()`, `SigningConfig.isV2SigningEnabled()`, `BaseArtifact.getPackageDependencies()`, `Variant.getTestedTargetVariants()`, `NativeArtifact.getTargetName()`, and `NativeAndroidProject.getBuildSystems()`. A later rerun compiled but still failed one JVM assertion in `Builder_modelTest.exposesVersionArtifactOutputAndSeverityConstants()` (`expected: 14 but was: 18`) in `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-23-11-749014Z.log`.\n\nAfter that, the fix appears to have converged: `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-23-43-038902Z.log`, `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-26-00-022149Z.log`, and `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-27-02-319939Z.log` all end in `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, with the later runs passing both JVM and native-image tests. The preserved commit is `1ca2af969a5016f25f5a27c3c23525caed4b8dd3`, but `stats/com.android.tools.build/builder-model/2.2.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `iterations: 2`, and `generated_loc: 0`, which does not match the preserved passing candidate. That points to a failure in result reporting/preservation logic rather than the test fix itself.\n\nLogs/files to inspect:\n- `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-20-48-280754Z.log`\n- `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-23-11-749014Z.log`\n- `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T20-27-02-319939Z.log`\n- `logs/com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-05T20-23-11-700313Z.log`\n- `stats/com.android.tools.build/builder-model/2.2.0/execution-metrics.json`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch/commit `1ca2af969a5016f25f5a27c3c23525caed4b8dd3` and confirm the test and metadata changes are acceptable.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.android.tools.build:builder-model:2.2.0` from the preserved branch to verify independently.\n3. If it still passes, promote the preserved commit manually and investigate the workflow finalizer/metrics reporting path that left the run in `failure` despite passing reruns."}}
